                <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aius</ex></expan> Valerius <lb n="2"/>Mel<expan><ex>e</ex><abbr>ager</abbr></expan> <lb n="3"/>miles c<expan><ex>o</ex><abbr>ho</abbr><ex>rtis</ex></expan> <lb n="4"/>XIIII <expan><abbr>urb</abbr><ex>anae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr><am><g type="centuria"/></am></abbr><ex>centuria</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>arci</ex></expan> <lb n="5"/>Gemelli He<lb break="no" n="6"/>rculi </ab></div><div n="2" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> <supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>otum</ex></expan></supplied> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>olvit</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>ibens</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>erito</ex></expan>
            </ab></div></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Das Stück stammt aus der Sammlung Cesar Bolliac in Bukarest. Z. 6 steht auf der crepido. Buchstabe E in Form von II geschrieben. (B): AE 1974: Z. 3: mil(es); AE 1972: Z. 4: XIII; AE 1974, CIL III: Z. 6: nicht gelesen; Russu, AE 1972: Z. 6: [v(otum) s(olvit)].</p>
            </div>
